        <abstract> 
<p>Discusses the role of ice in determining the geological features of the Jura. Mentions view of Agassiz. Objects to idea of "a [sea of ice] carrying rocks". Notes Agassiz’s earlier view of "ice expanded in the <hi rend="italic">line</hi> of the Great Swiss Valley". Comments on Pentlands.</p> 
        </abstract>
